<p>Your Mediator comes, you weak soul <br />
Of Moses‚Äô thund‚Äôrous curse afraid <br />
And in an anxious, grief-filled, deep hole <br />
By dark and gloomy shackles stayed! <br />
See! The Satanic chains are tearing <br />
Which your poor spirit were ensnaring! <br />
The bonds are loosed! The curse is done! <br />
For free salvation be now hoping. <br />
God is appeased, His heart stands open: <br />
Your gracious Mediator comes!</p>

<p>Your Teacher comes. Hear what He‚Äôs saying. <br />
Give ear to the mouth of the Lord. <br />
When lost, He is your way displaying. <br />
On you are light and truth outpoured. <br />
That which dark shadows were concealing <br />
