Your wise, all-knowing Teacher comes!</p>

<p>Your King now comes, but without fanfare. <br />
His entrance rich in poverty. <br />
Receive your Prince, who does as man share <br />
With you your deep humility! <br />
Come, then, and kiss His hand and scepter <br />
For since He is your sure Protector, <br />
The floods of fear can harm you none. <br />
And in a faithful subject‚Äôs manner <br />
Come swear yourself unto His banner: <br />
Your long-awaited King now comes!</p>

